@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

    - an amiga
    - ixemul.library v45.1+
    - an FPU is highly recommended.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"

4 versions supplied. Compiled with different gcc options. Rename to suit
your needs.

    amp.000    - any amiga
    amp.020    - 020+
    amp.020881 - 020+ with FPU (-m68020 -m68881)
    amp.040881 - 040 with FPU


Usage:
    amp <infile.mp3> <outfile.pcm>

    amp -w <infile.mp3> <outfile.wav>

Or just:
    amp
	to get a list of options.

Amiga Options
    -m  switch to mono mode
    -2  frequency divide by 2    (NB only available in MONO mode)
    -4  frequency divide by 4    (NB only available in MONO mode)



Warning! Mpeg audio files are often compressed at ratios greater than 10:1,
so you better make sure you have lots of HD space to decode them.

Note: I use Play16 to play back the audio files.

    play16 outfile.wav

If you output as PCM you will need to specify the type of file when
playing back with play16. eg

    play16 freq=44100 tracks=2 bits=16 spot1.pcm

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Playback" "Playback"

At the moment there are no amiga audio routines in the code.
To play the sound you must first decode to disk and then play with play16.
I tried fiddling with pipes and play16, but play16 won't play sound from a
pipe.  There may be other sound players out there you could try this with,
but i'm not certain.

When AHI V3 arrives I'm told we will have an AUDIO: device similar to AUD:
(audio-handler on aminet) but with support for 14bit 44khz playback.  Have
to wait and see.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Speed" "Speed"

The file spot1.mp3 has been used for timing tests. It is a 10.9 second
stereo 44.1khz 16bit sample.

v0.7.2 is a little slower than 0.7.1 due to more clipping tests.

25Mhz030/881 decodes it in 6minutes 50seconds.
    with -m       3minutes 46 seconds
    with -m -2    3minutes  5 seconds
    with -m -4    2mintues 55 seconds

[not super accurate timing]
[No other timings are available]

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Source" "Source"

The source code to amp was written by @{" tomislav uzelac " link "Acknowledgements"}

My changes to this source are in the src directory of this archive. Just
copy my files over the ones in the distribution.

Amiga changes are marked by -DMONO  and  -DFREQDIV

NB FREQDIV is only available if MONO is enabled.

I'll try and fix this in the next version.

My C coding isn't that strong, so if you see something I've done stupidly,
drop me a line on how to fix it or make it better.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Problems" "Problems"

    - Decoded sound files are corrupt
	amp doens't implement the full mpeg audio standard. In my
	experience, it seems to only cope properly with 44khz 16bit
	stereo samples. grab mus/misc/mp3.lha to get a full implementation
	decoder (mpeg3play is slower though)

    - It's slow.
	The mp3 algorithms are CPU intense. 
	Having an FPU helps a lot.
	
    - Immediate guru when run
	Make sure you have the latest ixemul.library from aminet.
	(version 45.1 is the latest)

    - EMT trap
	This will happen when you run a version of amp requiring an FPU
	but don't actually have an FPU on your machine.  Run a version that
	doesn't require an FPU.
	NB: the 020-040 version requires an FPU.

    - mp2 files corrupt
	At the moment this is an mp3 decoder only.

    - amp gurus just as it exits
	v0.7.0 used to give enforcer hits on exit. To my knowledge
	this no longer happens with v0.7.2

    - Frequency division is only available in MONO mode
	I'll try and fix this for the next version.

@ENDNODE

